HEADWORD: Plateau
<hw>Pla*teau"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> F.
<plw>Plateaux</plw> <pr>(F. <?/; E. <?/)</pr>, E.</plu>
<plw>Plateaus</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>. <ety>[F., fr. OF. <ets>platel</ets>,
properly a little plate. See <er>Plate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
flat surface; especially, a broad, level, elevated area of land; a
table-land.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An ornamental dish for the table; a tray or
salver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plateful</ent>⟦br⟧
